$ Windows service: WinRM

*Windows Remote Management (WS-Management)*

WinRM provides communications services for any number of applications.

WinRM has superseded DCOM as recommended remote → Windows/Management-Instrumentation[WMI] protocol.

WinRM builds upon (or implements) the WS-Man (Web Services Management) specification (or protocol) which is → development/web/service/SOAP[SOAP] based. *WS-Man* handles
communications ans authenticaions for connections.

The WinRM → Windows/services[service] listens on → development/web/TCP-IP[TCP/IP] port 5985 (by default).

